{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He had books in Russian and German and Polish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And one of the things that I remember very vividly is that he had George Eliot's book in Hebrew translation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I remember his books on Nietzsche, on philosophers, and, of course, all the books that he could collect in Yiddish and in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "He was especially fond of the poetry of Hayim Nahman Bialik, and he was very fond of Ahad Ha'am.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Ahad Ha'am was the first Jewish writer who decided to use the Hebrew language and revived the Hebrew language as a literary language in the 19th century.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So not only was-- did he enjoy being a scholar, but others enjoyed his scholarship as well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I recall that once a month he had meetings in his house of a number of people, usually four or five, among whom were two Catholic priests and one judge, who were obviously not Jewish, and who came there just to take advantage of his scholarship.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Coming through the house, going through the house, I also remember the bedrooms.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's and father's bedroom had a special attraction to me for two reasons.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother stored there her beautiful clothes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I was a young girl, I liked to go in and try on some of her clothes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She had her engagement gown, which was a pale blue, satin blue, trimmed in ermine fur, and I remember dressing up in it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the second thing that I remember about this bedroom, that she had custom-made furniture.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was inlaid in little pieces of mirror and mother of pearl around it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was a very beautiful kind of hand-crafted furniture.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, there were the children's bedrooms that were not exceptional, just bedrooms.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
